## 🌐 Remote VPS Deployment

Deploy Antigravity Workspace on your Ubuntu VPS in minutes!

### Quick Remote Deploy

```bash
# 1. SSH into your VPS
ssh user@your-vps-ip

# 2. Run the remote installer
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/primoscope/antigravity-workspace-template/main/install-remote.sh | bash

# 3. Add your API keys
nano .env

# 4. Start the workspace
./start.sh

# 5. Access from browser
# http://your-vps-ip
```

### What the Remote Installer Does

- ✅ **Installs all dependencies** (Node.js, Python, Docker)
- ✅ **Configures firewall** (ports 80, 443, 3000, 8000)
- ✅ **Sets up nginx** reverse proxy with error handling
- ✅ **Enables CORS** for remote access
- ✅ **Auto-SSL for seecast.cloud** (when AUTO_SSL_DOMAIN is set)
- ✅ **Optional SSL** with Let's Encrypt for any domain
- ✅ **Auto-configuration** for your VPS IP/domain
- ✅ **Validates installation** to ensure all components installed correctly

### Remote Access Features

- **Dynamic Host Detection**: Frontend automatically finds backend
- **CORS Configuration**: Supports wildcard or specific origins
- **WebSocket Support**: Real-time communication over remote connections
- **SSL/HTTPS Ready**: Easy setup with Let's Encrypt
- **Nginx Reverse Proxy**: Production-ready configuration included

📖 **[Complete Remote Deployment Guide →](docs/REMOTE_DEPLOYMENT.md)**

