## 📦 Quick Start

### Option 1: Automated Installation (Recommended for Ubuntu VPS)

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/primoscope/antigravity-workspace-template.git
cd antigravity-workspace-template

# Run automated installation
./install.sh

# Configure your environment
./configure.sh

# Start the workspace
./start.sh
```

### Option 2: Manual Setup

```bash
# 1. Install system dependencies
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y python3 python3-pip python3-venv nodejs npm docker.io

# 2. Create Python virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

# 3. Install Python dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install -r backend/requirements.txt

# 4. Install MCP servers
npm install -g @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem
npm install -g @modelcontextprotocol/server-git
npm install -g @github/mcp-server
# ... (see install.sh for complete list)

# 5. Configure environment
cp .env.example .env
nano .env  # Edit with your API keys

# 6. Start the backend
cd backend
python main.py
```

### Option 3: Docker Compose

```bash
# Start all services
docker-compose up -d

# View logs
docker-compose logs -f

# Stop services
docker-compose down
```

## 🔑 Configuration

### Required API Keys

Get your API keys from:
- **Gemini AI**: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
- **Vertex AI** (optional, enterprise-grade): https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
- **GitHub Token**: https://github.com/settings/tokens (scopes: `repo`, `read:org`)

### Configuration Wizard

Run the interactive configuration wizard:
```bash
./configure.sh
```

This will guide you through:
- ✅ Gemini AI setup
- ✅ Vertex AI setup (optional, for enterprise use)
- ✅ GitHub integration
- ✅ Local Ollama configuration
- ✅ Optional services (Brave Search, PostgreSQL, etc.)
- ✅ Server settings

### Manual Configuration

Edit `.env` file:
```bash
# AI Models
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

# Vertex AI (optional, for enterprise)
VERTEX_API_KEY=your_vertex_api_key_here
VERTEX_PROJECT_ID=your-gcp-project-id
VERTEX_LOCATION=us-central1
VERTEX_MODEL=gemini-pro

# Local Models
LOCAL_MODEL=llama3

# GitHub Integration
COPILOT_MCP_GITHUB_TOKEN=your_token_here

# Optional Services
COPILOT_MCP_BRAVE_API_KEY=
COPILOT_MCP_POSTGRES_CONNECTION_STRING=

# Server Configuration
HOST=0.0.0.0
PORT=8000
```

## 🎯 Usage

### Starting the Workspace

```bash
# Quick start (recommended)
./start.sh

# Or use systemd service
sudo systemctl start antigravity
sudo systemctl enable antigravity  # Auto-start on boot

# Or use Docker
docker-compose up -d
```

### Stopping the Workspace

```bash
# Quick stop
./stop.sh

# Or systemd
sudo systemctl stop antigravity

# Or Docker
docker-compose down
```

### Accessing the Interface

Open your browser and navigate to:
- **Web GUI**: http://localhost:8000 (or your server IP)
- **API Docs**: http://localhost:8000/docs
- **Health Check**: http://localhost:8000/health

### Using AI Agents

#### In the Web Interface
1. Select an agent from the right panel
2. Type your request in the chat
3. The selected agent will respond with expertise

#### With GitHub Copilot
```bash
# In GitHub Copilot Chat or IDE
@agent:full-stack-developer Create a REST API for user management
@agent:devops-infrastructure Set up Docker containers for this app
@agent:testing-stability-expert Write comprehensive tests
@agent:performance-optimizer Analyze and optimize performance
```

### Example Workflows

#### 1. Create a New Feature
```bash
@full-stack-developer Create a user authentication system with:
- JWT token-based auth
- Login/register endpoints
- Password hashing with bcrypt
- Session management
Include both backend API and frontend components
```

#### 2. Setup CI/CD Pipeline
```bash
@devops-infrastructure Create a GitHub Actions workflow that:
- Runs tests on Python 3.9, 3.10, 3.11
- Builds Docker images
- Deploys to staging on develop branch
- Deploys to production on main with approval
```

#### 3. Optimize Performance
```bash
@performance-optimizer Analyze the application and:
- Profile CPU and memory usage
- Identify bottlenecks
- Suggest optimization strategies
- Implement caching where appropriate
```

## 📊 Monitoring & Maintenance

### Health Check

```bash
# Run comprehensive validation
./validate.sh

# Check service status
sudo systemctl status antigravity

# View logs
sudo journalctl -u antigravity -f
```

### Performance Monitoring

Access performance metrics:
- **Health**: http://localhost:8000/performance/health
- **Metrics**: http://localhost:8000/performance/metrics
- **Analysis**: http://localhost:8000/performance/analysis

### Backup & Restore

```bash
# Backup data
tar -czf backup.tar.gz drop_zone/ data.db logs/ .env

# Restore data
tar -xzf backup.tar.gz
```

## 🏗️ Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    User[User] -->|Interacts| WebGUI[Web GUI]
    WebGUI -->|WebSocket| Backend[FastAPI Backend]
    
    subgraph "AI Intelligence Layer"
        Backend --> AgentManager[Agent Manager]
        AgentManager --> FSAgent[Full-Stack Agent]
        AgentManager --> DevOpsAgent[DevOps Agent]
        AgentManager --> TestAgent[Testing Agent]
        AgentManager --> PerfAgent[Performance Agent]
        
        FSAgent --> Gemini[Gemini AI]
        DevOpsAgent --> Gemini
        FSAgent --> Ollama[Local Ollama]
    end
    
    subgraph "MCP Server Layer"
        AgentManager --> MCP[MCP Servers]
        MCP --> FS[Filesystem]
        MCP --> Git[Git]
        MCP --> GitHub[GitHub]
        MCP --> Docker[Docker]
        MCP --> DB[Databases]
    end
    
    subgraph "Data Layer"
        Backend --> ChromaDB[(ChromaDB)]
        Backend --> Redis[(Redis)]
        Backend --> SQLite[(SQLite)]
    end
    
    Backend --> DropZone[Drop Zone]
    DropZone --> Watcher[File Watcher]
    Watcher --> Ingest[RAG Ingestion]
    Ingest --> ChromaDB
```

